  "prompt": "What are some great story books?",
  "response": "There are countless great storybooks across various genres and for different age groups. Here are some classic and contemporary recommendations:\n\n### For Young Children:\n1. **\"Where the Wild Things Are\" by Maurice Sendak** - A tale of adventure and imagination.\n2. **\"The Very Hungry Caterpillar\" by Eric Carle** - A delightful story that teaches counting and days of the week.\n3. **\"Goodnight Moon\" by Margaret Wise Brown** - A soothing bedtime story.\n\n### For Middle Grade Readers:\n1. **\"Harry Potter and the Sorcerer\u2019s Stone\" by J.K. Rowling** - The beginning of the epic tale of a young wizard.\n2. **\"Matilda\" by Roald Dahl** - The story of a brilliant girl with a love for books and a knack for magic.\n3. **\"Percy Jackson & the Olympians: The Lightning Thief\" by Rick Riordan** - A modern take on Greek mythology.\n\n### For Young Adults:\n1. **\"The Fault in Our Stars\" by John Green** - A poignant love story about two teens dealing with cancer.\n2. **\"The Hunger Games\" by Suzanne Collins** - A dystopian thriller centered on survival and rebellion.\n3. **\"Eleanor & Park\" by Rainbow Rowell** - A story of first love in the 1980s.\n\n### For Adults:\n1. **\"Pride and Prejudice\" by Jane Austen** - A classic romance with sharp social commentary.\n2. **\"1984\" by George Orwell** - A dystopian novel that explores themes of totalitarianism and freedom.\n3. **\"The Night Circus\" by Erin Morgenstern** - A magical realism novel that intertwines fantasy and romance.\n\n### Short Stories:\n1. **\"The Interpreter of Maladies\" by Jhumpa Lahiri** - A collection that explores the lives of Indian and Indian-American characters.\n2. **\"Dubliners\" by James Joyce** - A series of short stories depicting the lives of Dublin's residents.\n\n### Graphic Novels:\n1. **\"Maus\" by Art Spiegelman** - A Pulitzer Prize-winning graphic novel depicting the Holocaust.\n2. **\"Persepolis\" by Marjane Satrapi** - A memoir in graphic novel form about growing up during the Iranian Revolution.\n\nThese books span a variety of themes and styles, so there\u2019s something for everyone regardless of age or interests!",
